    <note>Zhao(1) Shichang(3) [22158] CBD identifies Shichang(3) as #2 son of Shouyue [19300], whereas he appears as the #3 son in the genealogical tables. Linghe [22164] is identified by CBD as a son of Shichang(3), whereas the genealogical tables have no sons for Shichang(3) and Linghe appears as the #9 son of Shimian(2) [22163], #2 son (in genealogical tables) of Shouyue. Linghe has two sons, Ziyu(2) [22165] and Zilun [22161] in the genealogical tables, whereas his funerary inscription only lists one son, Ziyu. Zilun is also listed in SS(PRC), 215.5710 as a great grandson of Shoujie [3210]. The genealogical tables list Boyi(2) [22166] as the only son of Ziyu(2) and list no sons for Zilun as #2 son of Linghe (but many sons for Zilun as great grandson of Shoujie), whereas the funerary inscription for Zilun's wife, born Wang, list Boyi(2) as her only son. Aside from massive errors, the only explanation is that Shichang(3) was childless and Linghe became his adopted heir, Linghe died young and #1 son Ziyu(2) died without heirs and Zilun's son by his wife, born Wang (probably not his first wife), Boyi(2), became the adopted heir of Ziyu(2) and Zilun was listed twice in error. The identifications are all in accord with the titles listed in the genealogical tables. SS(PRC), 215.5754. CBD, 4, 3423.</note>
